FBIS4-28658 "dreas113_a_94015" FBIS-EAS-94-113 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Reports on Issues Related to DPRK Continue Reports on Issues Related to DPRK Continue SDPJ Legislators Leave for Pyongyang OW1006042594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0353 GMT 10 Jun 94 OW1006042594 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, June 10 KYODO -- A delegation of legislators from the Social Democratic Party (SDP) left Japan on Friday [10 June] to visit north korea via Beijing. The legislators will arrive in Pyongyang on Saturday. They will hold talks with senior officials of the Korean Workers' Party on North Korea's nuclear issue before returning to Tokyo next Tuesday, SDP officials said. The SDP is Japan's second largest party after the Liberal Democratic Party, both in the opposition camp.
